text:
Ro: Hey guys, it’s Ro! Welcome to another
Nerdy Nummies!

Ro: Today I have a special guest, my really
good friend Trisha!

Trisha: Hey everyone, I’m so happy to be
here! And I have a big hint for you about

Trisha: what we’re gonna do… We’re gonna
do a Teemo cake!

Ro: Yes! For all of you League of Legends
fans, I have been getting so many

Ro: requests for something LoL, so today,
we are here to make those wishes
Ro: come true! Let’s get started!

Ro: The things you will need, will be: vegetable
oil, water, 1 cake mix,

Ro: I’m doing chocolate because it’s delicious.
3 eggs, and…

Trisha: 2 round mixing bowls, and these are
6 inches, and you need a big mixing bowl!

Ro: The biggest you can find! Trisha: And
a beater.
Ro: Yeah, let’s put it all together!

Ro: Now that we got all of our ingredients
together, it is time to mix, mix for
Ro: about 2 minutes on a medium speed!

Trisha: And have a helper to hold that bowl
for you.

Ro: Yeah, she’s gonna be my helper, she’s
gonna hold this thing down. Because
Ro: sometimes this gets crazy!
Trisha: Weee! Ro: Wooooh!

Ro: 1 for you, 1 for me! Trisha: Cheers! Hey,
oh! Ro: Oh, I was rude!
Ro: Oh I was rude! Trisha: Sike!

Ro: Once your batters mixed you’re gonna
take your 2 pans, and you’re gonna

Ro: grease ‘em, and you can either spray
them with cooking spray, or you can

Ro: use butter, whatever you’d like. Trisha:
Like hairspray!

Ro: Yeah, just like hairspray, you can just
pssssshhhhhh! Trisha: Oh!

Ro: And you can also spray your table, it
helps keep it nice and smooth!

Trisha: How much. Ro: That’s good. Trisha:
We’re good? Ro: That’s good!

Ro: Yeah, now you’re gonna pour your batter
in.

Ro: Pour about 1/2 of it, you’re trying
to eyeball it, you can do it Trisha!
Ro: You can do it!
Ro: Nice.

Trisha: You shouldn’t have me do this, you
know I dropped my own birthday cake before!

Trisha: Once you’re all set you’re gonna
take these and heat them in the oven
Trisha: at 350 for 20 minutes.

Ro: Yeah, just keep your eye on them, you
don’t want them to burn, these are a

Ro: little bit smaller, they’re only a 6
inch pan so, just keep your eye on ‘em!

Ro: 20 minutes should be just fine. Yum-yum-yum!
Trisha: Yum-yum-yum!
Both: Om-nom-nom-nom-nom!

Ro: Once your cakes are all one cooling, make
sure that they are not warm anymore,

Ro: They’ve had plenty of time to cool.
We are going to level our cakes using this.

Trisha: Not leveling like gaming right? Ro:
No, no, not leveling like gaming.

Ro: This is actually taking points off…
Trisha: OK. Ro: We’re taking the top

Ro: of the cake off. Trisha: Show me how it’s
done.

Ro: OK, so this is what you do, there’s
different settings, they’re an inch apart.

Ro: And I have it on the lowest setting, you’re
just gonna hold the top, and then

Ro: you’re gonna saw back and forth and
you’re gonna go all the way through the

Ro: cake so that both of the cakes are the same
height.
Trisha: Ohhhh! Ro: Ree-ree-ree-ree-ree-ree-ree-ree!

Trisha: And you definitely have to make those
noises. Ro: If you don’t it won’t work!
Trisha: It won’t work.

Ro: Once your cakes are leveled, you’re
gonna take 1 of them and put them in

Ro: the middle of this circle. I just cut
a circle out of the cardboard cake tray…

Trisha: Thing. Ro: I can talk… Thing! And
Trisha’s gonna take her weapon of choice.

Trisha: Bew! Ro: Pewm! The Mustach-ula. The
Mustach-ula!

Ro: And I’ve just got chocolate frosting
and fresh raspberries because I…

Ro: I’m on this kick where I put fruit in-between
the cakes, it’s so good!

Trisha: You know this reminds me of Nutella.
Ro: Yeah, and it smells just like it!
Ro: Ooooh, you could use Nutella in this!

Trisha: The first time I ever ate Nutella I fisted
it. Ro: Did you?

Trisha: Yeah I put my whole hand in the jar!
It was so good!

Trisha: I, I’m not gonna fist your bowl.
Ro: OK…

Ro: Now you’re gonna take your fresh raspberries
and sprinkle them on top of the
Ro: frosting before we put on our second cake.

Ro: Oooh, take a look at that! Once you got
your cake all frosted you’re gonna

Ro: put it in the freezer for about 10 minutes
to let it chill before we put
Ro: the fondant on top!

Both: Fondant time! Fondant time! Fondant
time! Fondant time! Fondant time!

Ro: Fondant time! Trisha: Fondant! Ro: Trisha’s
got these 2 molds.

Ro: She’s Vanna-ing them, you found them
at? Trisha: I found them at Michael’s,

Trisha: and they’re Wilton brand. Ro: Yes
Wilton brand, they have these really

Ro: cool fondant molds, and these are the
ones I used for the castle cake, so if

Ro: you ever wanted to reference that video,
go check it out. This ones wood

Ro: and this ones a stone! So for the wood
you’re gonna take the brown

Ro: fondant and press it in here, I’m just
taking a little piece so you can see

Ro: what this will look like. Press down,
then when you lift it up you’ll have

Ro: this really cool wooden print. So what
I did is I just made a bunch of brown

Ro: squares out of the fondant with the wood
print in them, and then we’re gonna

Ro: wrap them around the cake when the cake
is ready.

Ro: And then for the gray fondant, we’re
just gonna roll it out, and then we’re

Ro: gonna take the stone mold, and press it
on top, I’ll let you do it, put your

Ro: muscles on it, just press down. Trisha:
Ewagh! Ro: She’s got gamer muscles!

Ro: I like it! Trisha: Oh! Ro: Oh isn’t
that cool?

Ro: So once you have the imprint I’m just
gonna take this little tool, you can use a

Ro: knife or a scissor or whatever you want,
I found this little tool.

Ro: And you’re gonna cut out a little shape,
so it looks like natural stone, a

Ro: little natural stone patch that he’s
gonna be sitting on. Trisha: Ohhhh!

Ro: Here is what the stones look like all
cut out. You can make it any shape that

Ro: you like, I just kind of picked this weird
shape.

Ro: And now we’re gonna make little rocks,
I made a bunch of them over here so you

Ro: can see what they look like. You’re
just gonna roll ‘em and try to make them

Ro: uneven, so they aren’t a perfect circle,
because rocks are not perfect shape.

Trisha: They’re not perfect! Ro: And the
last thing we made were little mushrooms,

Ro: so we just used green fondant with little
purple fondant on the top and again

Ro: chocolate fondant on the bottom. Trisha:
Ooooh! Ro: To make the little mushrooms,

Ro: here! Trisha: They’re little Teemo mushrooms!
Ro: Aren’t they so cute?
Ro: I was like, these are adorable!

Ro: We just took the cake out of the freezer,
and now we are gonna assemble

Ro: all the parts. The first thing that you’re
gonna do is take our wood fondant

Ro: pieces and lay them all the way around,
and then we’re gonna take…

Ro: Errr. Trisha: Frosting! Ro: Our green
frosting, this is just a vanilla

Ro: buttercream frosting that we dyed green
with food coloring.

Ro: And I’ll show you the tip, and I’ll
take off this little tape, so, as you

Ro: can see, it has 1 of these little tips
so that when you squeeze it out it will

Ro: look like grass. We’re gonna put grass
on the cake plate and grass on the top.

Ro: So we have all the details on the
cake, but the last thing we need to add

Ro: is… Trisha: Teemo! Ro: Teemo! So I made
this, ta-da! Out of fondant, I just sat

Ro: there and sculpted it like you would a
little, a little sculpture.

Trisha: A little Yordle. Ro: A little Yordle!
Trisha: A little Yordle!

Ro: They look like hamsters to me with tails,
but…
Trisha: But, I had to tell her it’s a Yordle!

Ro: Yeah, she had to tell me it’s not a
hamster! But I was like, no I’m gonna name

Ro: him Hammy! But here he is, he’s so cute
and he’s holding a little cupcake!

Ro: And we’re just gonna put him right here
in the center of the cake and then

Ro: Ta-da! Trisha: Ta-da! Ro: We’re all
done!

Both: Ta-da! Ro: Here’s our League of Legends
Teemo Cake, I hope you guys like it!

Ro: It was so much fun to make and he’s
so cute!

Trisha: Yeah I love it! He’s so cute! He’s
just a little guy!
Both: Go Teemo, go Teemo, go Teemo, go Teemo!

Ro: And, thank you to Trisha for being here,
she is amazing and I love her!

Ro: And I will put all of her links down below
so you can go check her out.

Ro: Her YouTube and Twitter and twitch, she
live-streams, she’s 1 of my favorite
Ro: gamers. She’s super good!

Trisha: Yeah, I just want to say thanks so
much, I love you Ro, and you guys have

Trisha: been requesting a lot of League stuff
right? Ro: Mmmhmmm.

Trisha: So I was like, yeah! I’ve been doing
my Bear Cup Tournaments, usually I

Trisha: do things for Starcraft, but I’ve
been playing lots of League.

Trisha: So I’m gonna start a new Bear Cup
tournament that’s gonna be a

Trisha: 1v1 and we’ll make sure that’s
posted too!

Ro: Yeah, I’ll put that down there so you
can check that out too. She is awesome,

Ro: she actually hosts gaming tournaments!
Trisha: Yeah. Ro: Yes!

Trisha: I hope you guys join! Ro: So please
go check her out, she’s 1 of my

Ro: favorites. Thanks you guys! And if you
have any other ideas for any other

Ro: Nerdy Nummies… Trisha: I always have
a delay.
Ro: She’s so good, she makes me laugh!

Ro: Please let me know, leave me a link down
below and I will
Ro: do my best to make it happen!
Ro: OK, bye-bye!
